```

The key points of how this works:

`word.DisplayAlerts = 0` suppresses the "unreadable content" popup entirely — Word processes it silently in the background with no UI shown to the user.

`Repair=False` means if Word has to repair it, the open call throws an exception instead of silently fixing it — so you catch corruption that would otherwise be hidden.

`doc.Words.Count` forces Word to fully parse the entire document, not just the header — lazy loading would miss corruption deep in the body.

`save_and_validate()` is the one-liner to drop into your existing pipeline right after `val_report.save()`.
